      "type": "feature",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>Before the PCs depart Stairwatch, Solvi presses a coal-ember in a small iron box into their hands. \"Take this. It's not much. But... don't let the fire die. Please.\" The coal-ember can be used once to ignite a campfire that burns warm for 8 hours regardless of weather conditions (automatic success on one fire-related montage test). After use, the coal goes dark and the box grows cold.</p>",
          "director": "<p>Play this moment for emotional weight. The mechanical benefit is real â€” automatic success on one fire-related montage test â€” but the players will remember a scared girl handing heroes her last scrap of hope. Don't remind the party it exists. Let them remember Solvi's gift on their own. When they do, it hits harder.</p>"
        },
        "source": {
