    "biography": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Solvi</strong> is the Ember-Keeper of Stairwatch â€” a frightened teenager chosen for the role only six months ago. She tends the town's Ever-Ember: barely a campfire at the central crossroads.</p><p>Despite her fear, Solvi is dutiful. She approaches the PCs before their departure and presses a coal-ember in a small iron box into their hands. \"Take this. It's not much. But... don't let the fire die. Please.\"</p>",
      "director": "<p>Solvi appears in <strong>Beat 5, Part 7</strong> (Departure from Stairwatch). She represents the next generation forced into impossible roles.</p><p>Play her gift moment for emotional weight: a frightened teenager handing heroes the last scrap of warmth she has. The Ever-Ember she tends should be described as worryingly small. If the PCs ask about it, her eyes go wide and she changes the subject. She knows it's dying. She doesn't know what to do.</p>",
